hornsby's accordion on rider bit of a smoking hot second.i always thought hornsby brought a nice to the band when he played with them and i love the accordion sounds on i know you rider.good second set.a+ sound although jerrys vocals seem 2 bit a low at times from most likely not singing directly in the mic but pulling away to soon at times.
Jerry's the only one who remembers how to play China Cat lol Weir has long since ditched his part, leaving it to the 2 or 3 keyboard players what a mess!
Good 93' Hey well what can you expect for a 90's show this one has very nice sound quality and ive always loved Hornsby so that why its getting 5 stars(~):)

Very strong show I've been catching up on listening to shows I attended.  This is a true winner... nice run of shows generally.

First set is very solid. One of the first Broken Arrows, and Music is smoking hot.

The whole second set is very solid, even with excessive accordion to deal with.  Great China>Rider and Terrapin, especially.

Beautiful soundboard, too.
Above Average 93 Highlights: Terrapin Jam, I Fought The Law

Fading memories It’s sad that most of my memories of shows are gone or fading. But I’ll always hold on to some of them. Remember driving like a maniac after school from Philly to Landover And made it, missed maybe half of bucket I think. Shrooming face lol. One of the better shows I saw, it’s all relative, I only saw maybe a dozen good ones before Jerry’s nosedive starting in early 94, although at the end of 93 you can see signs of it. listening to the shows Now as soundboards you hear all the missed notes etc. There were hints of his decline at the end of 93. Summer 93 he was great but in fall especially with that new clean guitar and new sound every flaw could be heard. I hate that guitar that he had starting fall 93 Tiger was so much better. But fall 93 was still decent he was still Jerry, come spring 94 it was a totally different jerry And therefore band. No longer could play the guitar or sing, but especially the guitar was just abysmal very sad. Listen to any random show from Summer 93 and compare it with one from Summer 94 and you will see when I mean if you havent already noticed this. People tend to lump everything after 90 or 91 together but that is not true, it’s from 93 to 94 where things completely changed. Yes 1993 or 1992 don’t compare with 1990, but he was still Jerry up until the end of 93. Anyway I digress, back to the show. I rate the shows relative to the time They occurred, solid four stars for this one. Other commenters like the sound on this but I do not, Jerry’s guitar is very low and Phils base is too loud throughout. And you can’t hear Bobby’s guitar at all. seems like many of the soundboards from this era Have this problem of very uneven levels, I think maybe it was after Healy got fired that sound quality declined. At the shows and on the recordings. Not sure when his departure was though I could be wrong about that
Bruce  Long way to go home real high energy. Great set list and Bruce sit in but not as good of a show as the nights before
